{% extends 'base/base.html.twig' %}

{% block title %}Home{% endblock %}

{% block body %}

    <div class="section">

        <h1>Wase Engine</h1>

        <p>Wase Engine is an open source 2d game library made with C++ and the SDL libraries. Wase Engine can be used to create all kinds of 2d games. The main goal for Wase Engine is to give you the tools you need for creating games while keeping as much control as possible.</p>

    </div>

    <div class="section">

        <h2>Documentation</h2>

        <p>To find out more about how Wase Engine works you can head over to the <a href="{{ path('documentation') }}">documentation</a> page.</p>

    </div>

    <div class="section">

        <h2>Contributing</h2>

        <p>Wase Engine is completely open source and free to use. We love it when other people help and contribute to the source code of Wase Engine. To start contributing to Wase Engine you should read the
            <a href="https://github.com/JelleVos1/wase-engine/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md" target="_blank">contributing</a> page.</p>

    </div>

    <div class="section">

        <h2>Latest builds</h2>

        <table>
            <thead>
                <th>Name</th>
                <th>Release date</th>
                <th>Links</th>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                {% for release in releases %}
                    <tr>
                        <td>{{ release.name }}</td>
                        <td>{{ release.published_at | date('d M Y, H:i:s') }}</td>
                        <td><a href="{{ release.zipball_url }}">{{ release.name }}</a></td>
                    </tr>
                {% endfor %}
                {% if releases is empty %}
                    <tr><td colspan="3">No builds available</td></tr>
                {% endif %}
            </tbody>
        </table>

        <a href="{{ path('builds') }}">See all builds</a>

    </div>

{% endblock %}
